# FlipSentry UI Port

## Scope

- Work in **heroui-mobile** only for implementation.
- **mobile-app** is screen/flow reference only - do not copy NativeWind, shadcn, or UI stacks from that app.

## Data & state

- Dual mode via `EXPO_PUBLIC_USE_MOCK` / `extra.useMock` (see `src/api/config.ts`).
- Preferred path: screens → MobX `src/store/*` → `src/api/agent.ts` → mock services **or** live HTTP (`src/api/http/*`).
- Screens must not branch on `USE_MOCK`; only the agent façade switches implementations.
- Persist mock domain data with AsyncStorage via `src/lib/storage.ts` when it must survive reload.
- Pure rules (slot math, intervals) live in `src/domain/*` — not in screens.
- Feed SignalR is allowed via `src/api/signalr/*` + `FeedStore` (live only). No Adapty in this pass. Axios is allowed only inside `src/api/http/*`.
- MobX is allowed; keep stores **split by domain** (UserStore, CommonStore, SearchStore, SubscriptionStore).
- Search / slot rules: see `SEARCH_STORE.md` (Starter / Hunter / Master tables).
- GroupSearch: **basic radius only** — no advanced/point polygon mode, no population heatmap.

## Theme

- Uber-inspired neutrals via HeroUI tokens in `src/global.css` (oklch grayscale).
- Dark: near-black background, white `--accent` / black `--accent-foreground`.
- Light: light gray background, black `--accent` / white `--accent-foreground`.
- Prefer semantic classes (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `bg-accent`) - no legacy green/black hardcodes (`#1DB954`, `#121212`).
- Use `Button variant="secondary"` for most actions; primary/accent sparingly (Uber black/white).

## Components

- Prefer `heroui-native-pro`, then `heroui-native` (OSS), then minimal custom (e.g. map placeholder).
- Do not use web `@heroui/react` / `@heroui-pro/react` for screens.
- Style with Uniwind `className` only — **never** `StyleSheet` / NativeWind (see `no-stylesheet.mdc`).
- Always check HeroUI MCP docs for how a component is meant to be used before inventing custom layout.

## Agent workflow

- Before building a screen, use Native Pro MCP: `list_components` → `get_component_docs`.
- Follow `PORTING.md` folder layout and port order (shell → auth → feed → home → settings → subscription).
